Business Brief -- Data-Design Laboratories Inc.:
   Banks Agree to Restructure
   Debt Totaling $14.1 Million
Data Design, a maker of computer circuit boards, said the
agreement also grants to the lenders an interest in the
majority of the company's assets and provides that the
company will maintain certain financial covenants.
   "This restructuring will provide additional working
capital to allow us to more fully utilize . . . equipment and
return management's primary focus to the growth of our core
businesses," said William E. Cook, president and chief
executive.